Blown out sign post Hurricane Irma in Bradenton FL. We spent 3 nights in the public shelter at Brandon River High school. With Robyn, my mom and our cat Neo. Feeling blessed. It was 5 days of tough decision making to safeguard loved ones, based on best available but ever changing information. 
Friends of ours wanted to go in the shelter, then changed their minds and boarded up their place with mattresses planning to ride it out, then got spooked and got on the road with little time to spare, getting gas on deserted country roads by good fortune, fleeing north, eventually making it to Georgia and then North Carolina. 
We weren't sure whether we made the right decision to stay in place and go into a shelter, all of Bradington basically being in one flood zone or another. We feel very fortunate, and unexpected jumps of the hurricane track sort of saved us, this time. I understand now why most people just board up their home and get out of town.

People at the shelter were just awesome. All these Latino families with 5 coolers, food and drink  Avocado dip and chips, and a ton of children playing in the hallways. So prepared! We felt like rank amateurs at survival. 
At one point the kids used a high school map of the world to play meteorologist and create a Hurricane tracks from pins and strings, so cute, and cheering all of us up. 
Good convos with National guardsmen, green keepers, nursing aids and a whole lot of people I'd never have met elsewhere. I need to get out more. 
Especially when there's a hurricane coming:)
#photooftheday #irma #hurricaneirma #lucky

Another real estate shot, amazing property right on the beach on the Jersey Shore. I love the fall solitude and vast empty beaches, almost spooky! On a technical note, for me the best shots are not "obvious" drone shots, or shots taking from above, for me the nest angles happen only a few feet above the roof line, plus it curbs the foreshortening effect. #realestate #luxuryrealestate #realtorlife #inspiration #architecture #villa #luxuryhome #aerialphotography #realestateinvestor
